http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Coimbatore/Women-cheated/article14008717.ece

Two men posing as policemen cheated two women at Tatabad here on Monday.They approached Jayalakshmi (53), and her sister Rajammal (48), of Sundapalayam, who were walking towards a hospital asking them to safeguard their jewellery.They told them to keep the gold chains covered in a piece of paper and volunteered to do so.When they reached home they found that the packet given to them contained stones.The police said that one of them was wearing a chain weighing about 32 gm, and the other about 24 gm. The police were trying to collect CCTV recordings to identify the accused.